import { Meta, Canvas } from '@storybook/addon-docs' import { registerTransitionalStyles } from '../../../../../dist/libs/core/src/transitional-styles.js' # Date picker Date pickers simplify the task of selecting a date in a visual representation of a calendar. The date picker in Green Core mimics the behaviour of the native date input element as it is implemented in Chromium browsers. The input field shows three parts of the date: the day, the month and the year. The user can navigate between these parts using the arrow keys. The user can also navigate between the parts by clicking on them or tabbing. When a part has focus, it can be changed using the arrow keys or by typing a number. Clicking the calendar icon opens a popover with a calendar view where a date can be chosen.
Chosen date: None
## Basic usage The date picker takes a `label` attribute for setting the label text, and has two slots for adding additional information. The `sub-label` slot sits between the label and the input, and the `message` slot sits below the input. The `message` slot is used to display instructions and/or validation errors. When the value is changed by a user, a `change` event is fired.
A sub-label can be added as additional description Instructive message. Will turn red if there is a validation error
## Other attributes In this example, all the available attributes are used.
A sub-label can be added as additional description Instructive message. Will turn red if there is a validation error

/* rules for groups of checkboxes and radio buttons*/
:host {
  display: block;
}

label {
  display: block;
  font-weight: 500;
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
}

label + .field {
  margin-top: 0.5rem;
}

.form-info {
  color: var(--text-primary-color);
  display: block;
  font-size: 0.875rem;
  line-height: 1.25rem;
  width: 100%;
}

.field {
  border-radius: var(--sg-border-radius);
  align-items: center;
  background-color: var(--sg-form-control-bg);
  box-sizing: border-box;
  color: var(--sg-text-primary);
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
  margin: 0.5rem 0;
  min-height: 2.75rem;
}
.field .input {
  padding-left: 1rem;
  padding-right: 1rem;
  padding-bottom: 0.75rem;
  padding-top: 0.75rem;
  border-top: solid var(--sg-border-width) var(--sg-border-color);
  border-bottom: solid var(--sg-border-width) var(--sg-border-color);
  border-left: solid var(--sg-border-width) var(--sg-border-color);
  --border-color: var(--sg-border-color);
  border-radius: var(--sg-border-radius) 0 0 var(--sg-border-radius);
  flex-grow: 1;
  isolation: isolate;
}
.field .input:focus:not(:focus-visible) {
  box-shadow: none;
  outline: 0;
}
.field .input:focus, .field .input:focus-within {
  outline-color: var(--gds-sys-color-focus-outline);
  outline-style: solid;
  outline-width: 0.125rem;
  outline-offset: 0.125rem;
}
.field span {
  cursor: default;
}
.field [role=spinbutton] {
  cursor: default;
  display: inline-block;
}
.field [role=spinbutton]:focus {
  background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--gds-sys-color-blue) 50%, transparent);
  outline: none;
}
.field button {
  -webkit-appearance: none;
     -moz-appearance: none;
          appearance: none;
  background: var(--intent-info-background);
  border: 0;
  border-radius: 0 var(--sg-border-radius) var(--sg-border-radius) 0;
  box-sizing: border-box;
  cursor: pointer;
  padding: 0.7rem 1rem;
  width: 3rem;
}
.field button:focus:not(:focus-visible) {
  box-shadow: none;
  outline: 0;
}
.field button:focus, .field button:focus-visible {
  outline-color: var(--gds-sys-color-focus-outline);
  outline-style: solid;
  outline-width: 0.125rem;
  outline-offset: 0.125rem;
}
.field button svg path {
  fill: #fff;
}

:host(:invalid) .field + .form-info {
  position: relative;
  transition: all 200ms ease-in-out, outline-offset 0s, outline-width 0s;
  color: var(--intent-danger-background);
  opacity: 1;
}
:host(:invalid) .field + .form-info::before {
  background: transparent;
  border-radius: 0 0 4px 4px;
  -webkit-clip-path: inset(4px 0 0 0);
          clip-path: inset(4px 0 0 0);
  content: "";
  display: block;
  height: 4px;
  position: absolute;
  transform: translate3d(0, -12px, 0);
  transition: 300ms ease-in-out;
  width: 100%;
}
:host(:invalid) .field + .form-info::before {
  background: var(--intent-danger-background);
  -webkit-clip-path: inset(1px 0 0 0);
          clip-path: inset(1px 0 0 0);
}

.header {
  padding-top: 0.5rem;
  padding-left: 0.5rem;
  padding-right: 0.5rem;
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
}
.header > * {
  margin-left: 0.25rem;
  margin-right: 0.25rem;
  min-width: auto;
}
.header > *.link {
  flex: 1 1;
}
.header button {
  -webkit-appearance: none;
     -moz-appearance: none;
          appearance: none;
  background: transparent;
  border: 0;
  cursor: pointer;
  padding: 0.7rem 1rem;
  width: 3rem;
}
.header button .icon::before {
  background: none;
  border-bottom: 2px solid;
  border-left: 2px solid;
  content: "";
  display: block;
  height: 12px;
  margin-top: 2px;
  width: 12px;
}
.header button .icon.prev::before {
  margin-left: -4px;
  transform: translate(75%) rotate(45deg) scaleZ(-1);
}
.header button .icon.next::before {
  margin-left: -10px;
  transform: translate(75%) rotate(-135deg) scaleZ(-1);
}

.footer {
  padding-left: 0.5rem;
  padding-right: 0.5rem;
  padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
  padding-top: 0.5rem;
  border-top: solid var(--sg-border-width) var(--sg-border-color);
  border-color: #ddd;
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
}
.footer button {
  border-radius: var(--sg-border-radius);
  -webkit-appearance: none;
     -moz-appearance: none;
          appearance: none;
  background: transparent;
  border: 0;
  color: var(--intent-info-background);
  cursor: pointer;
  font-family: inherit;
  font-weight: 500;
  padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
}
.footer button:hover {
  background: var(--intent-info-background);
  color: #fff;
